\[\frac{|4P_x - 7P_y + 4P_z - 25|}{\sqrt{4^2 + 7^2 + 4^2}} = \frac{|4P_x - 7P_y + 4P_z - 25|}{\sqrt{57}}.\]By the triangle inequality,
\[\frac{|4P_x - 7P_y + 4P_z - 25|}{\sqrt{57}} \ge \frac{|4 \cdot 5 - 7 \cdot 5 + 4 \cdot 0 - 25|}{\sqrt{57}} = \frac{5}{\sqrt{57}}.\]Hence, the maximal area of the cross-section is $\left( 2 \cdot \frac{5}{\sqrt{57}} \right)^2 = \boxed{\frac{500}{57}}.$

